pm.traitsDriversMessage: New 2018 norms underpinning the Traits and Drivers now enable you to choose between a global or location-specific norm - useful if you use Success Profiles to run assessments. We've upgraded all Success Profiles to the latest norms, whilst retaining any adjustments you may have made. You may notice some changes to the resulting traits and driver scores. We have not updated the traits and drivers used in any assessment projects.

pm.description: Set up your and any associated company's data by creating Parent and Subsidiary profiles. This can be used in various parts of the Talent Hub for different purposes such as grading Executive Success Profiles.

pm.execAboutModalContent: Executive Profile Grading is the functionality that allows your company to size senior people-leadership roles. This is based on the organization's details such as its revenue, the number of employees and ownership rather than on accountabilities like for non-executive roles.
pm.execDeleteConfirmationModalContentsub: Are you sure you want to delete? All data will be removed permanently and users will lose the ability to fit the executive level jobs to this company.
pm.execSaveIncompleteModalContentparent: All fields are required in order to enable the Executive Grading. Executive Grading will be disabled for all Success Profiles. Would you like to complete the required fields or continue saving?
pm.execSaveIncompleteModalContentsubsidi: All fields are required in order to enable Executive Grading. If you proceed, users will not be able to select this Subsidiary when grading Executive Profiles. The Parent information is also required to enable Executive Grading. Would you like to complete the required fields or continue saving?
